[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T22:15:02+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A TUAW website author profile for a Christina Warren, with her bio.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/18jMnu36D0gGHwvhOelWDViJHt8=/0x0:657x438/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73454011/450578836_368777242581587_423121686776513279_n__1_.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Christina Warren hasn\u2019t worked at this website since 2009, and that\u2019s not her face.</em> | Screenshot by Christina Warren</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"uYU8Gz\">An old Apple blog and the blog\u2019s former authors have become the latest victims of AI-written sludge. TUAW (\u201cThe Unofficial Apple Weblog\u201d) was <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2015/1/30/7949485/aol-shutting-down-tuaw-apple\">shut down by AOL in 2015</a>, but this past year, a new owner scooped up the domain and began posting articles under the bylines of former writers <em>who haven\u2019t worked there for over a decade.</em> And that new owner, which also appears to run other AI sludge websites, seems to be trying", "id": 843984, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195858/tuaw-unofficial-apple-tech-blog-ai-web-orange-khan", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Early Apple tech bloggers are shocked to find their name and work have been AI-zombified", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T20:55:52+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Timmy &amp;amp; Tommy\u2019s Aloha Edition bundle box.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/b4RUb81PMWmJuWRIXGSNfZu_S5I=/0x0:1779x1186/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73453846/Nintendo_Switch_Lite__Timmy___Tommy_s_Aloha_Edition__Press_Box_Image.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Walmart\u2019s exclusive Switch Lite deal includes a digital copy of</em> Animal Crossing: New Horizons<em>.</em> | Image: Nintendo</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ipIB7X\">From terrific deals on <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/8/24194403/apple-macbook-air-m1-laptop-walmart-early-access-deal-sale\">MacBooks</a> to the <a href=\"https://goto.walmart.com/c/482924/565706/9383?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FSuper-Mario-Party-Red-Blue-Joy-Con-Bundle%2F5216937998&amp;subId2=[]vg[p]23958985[i]dKTYWe[t]w[r]https://www.theverge.com/good-deals[d]D\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Super Mario Party</em> Joy-Con bundle</a>, <a href=\"https://ww", "id": 843695, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195708/walmart-nintendo-switch-lite-timmy-tommys-aloha-edition-animal-crossing-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Animal Crossing-inspired Nintendo Switch Lite is down to its best price yet", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T18:55:42+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the Amazon logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/a5NY6y8r1jJ5PXajDI4k9zuUtok=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73453660/acastro_STK103__02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"3Juajm\">Amazon\u2019s carbon emissions decreased slightly in 2023 after the company ramped up renewable energy purchases and cut down on pollution from construction, hardware, and equipment, according to its latest <a href=\"https://sustainability.aboutamazon.com/\">sustainability report</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"gvNSK7\">Back in 2019, Amazon pledged to reach net zero carbon emissions by 2040. Despite that goal, its carbon emissions actually <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/8/1/23287351/amazon-climate-change-carbon-emissions-worse-2021\">ballooned</a> soon after \u2014 climbing from around 51 million metric tons of CO2 in 2019 to more than 71 million metric tons in 2021. Now it seems", "id": 842896, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195707/amazons-carbon-emissions-fell-last-year", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Amazon\u2019s carbon emissions fell last year", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T18:18:08+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Google logo with colorful shapes\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/HilBGd_9o3jBCWNGbMeBbaETez0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73453596/STK093_Google_04.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Google\u2019s service lets you order your photos to go.</em> | Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"uTV6OX\">Apple and Google are offering a new, nearly painless way to copy files from Google Photos to iCloud. As <a href=\"https://9to5mac.com/2024/07/10/transfer-from-google-photos-to-icloud-photos/\">spotted by <em>9to5Mac</em></a>, Google is <a href=\"https://dtinit.org/blog/2024/07/10/DTI-members-new-photo-video-tool\">adding iCloud support</a> to its data transfer tool over the next week, making it possible to move your photo library directly to Apple\u2019s service \u2014 no download necessary. It\u2019s part of a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/7/20/17589246/data-transfer-project-google-facebook-microsoft-twitter\">bigger data p", "id": 842897, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195796/google-photos-transfer-to-icloud", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Switching from Google Photos to iCloud is about to be a lot less painful", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T18:15:52+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the Microsoft wordmark on a green background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TDgqkDd1OA3XGy12L04Gybl_vIE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73453584/STK095_Microsoft_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"HOO5gE\">Microsoft has reached a settlement with an industry group backed by European cloud infrastructure providers, quelling an antitrust battle that could have embroiled it for years and resulted in fines. But if Microsoft doesn\u2019t hold up its end of the bargain in the next nine months, the group has promised to revive its antitrust complaint with the European Commission.</p>\n<p id=\"L2AneR\">The group, Cloud Infrastructure Service Providers in Europe (CISPE), agreed to withdraw its <a href=\"https://cispe.cloud/cispe-files-complaint-against-microsoft-with-european-commission/\">2022 complaint to the European Commission</a>, where it accused Microsoft of ", "id": 842898, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195772/microsofts-cloud-licensing-deal-cispe-eu-antitrust", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft has nine months to stop another antitrust battle from escalating", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T17:48:30+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"yellow ford capri\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/iNNQYn3t0ZzxxXpEifCK14sthxA=/0x0:1979x1319/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73453480/2024Ford_ElectricCapri_15A.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Ford</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"sDQ9v1\">Ford\u2019s classic Capri coupe is <a href=\"https://media.ford.com/content/fordmedia/feu/en/news/2024/07/10/new-all-electric-capri.html\">returning as a four-door electric vehicle</a> with a profile resembling other chunky-looking electric crossovers like the Polestar 2. </p>\n<p id=\"XJG5YP\">Ford Europe design director Amko Leenarts <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/clip/UgkxJcVopS610I8prX6qU-5UwR8ClW0tf5YG\">says the look</a> follows an imagined evolution of the Capri since production ended in 1986, as inspired by the rising popularity of SUVs.</p>\n<p id=\"wzd5QB\">This beefier Capri follows Ford\u2019s other modern takes on classic nameplates, including the Mustang, which became an electric SUV, and the M", "id": 842581, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195756/ford-capri-ev-crossover-announce-europe", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_