&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F7%2F10%2F24195692%2Fmeta-quest-approved-contacts-parental-controls\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">upcoming change</a> will let parents individually approve each user their 10- to 12-year-old can call, chat with, and join VR experiences with on Quest. Previously, Met", "id": 841551, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195692/meta-quest-approved-contacts-parental-controls", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Meta will now let young kids chat in VR \u2014 but only with their parents\u2019 approval", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T15:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Richard Jacobs and Sergio Acevedo in Quad Gods\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/byh1xfCXIbeSwr7jCL_1cvtotX0=/76x0:904x552/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73453079/richard_jacobs_left_sergio_acevedo_right_.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Courtesy of HBO</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Director Jess Jacklin talks to The Verge about her new documentary following the first all-quadriplegic esports team.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24195198/quad-gods-documentary-jess-jacklin-interview\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 841552, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24195198/quad-gods-documentary-jess-jacklin-interview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The first all-quadriplegic esports team levels the playing field", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T14:35:02+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Hyundai dealership\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-d_KzeXYCLmcb__dQ2F1O6y8GiI=/107x0:1253x764/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73453039/2020_11_05.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Napelton Aurora Imports</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"umRGQm\">Hyundai pressured its dealers to \u201cartificially inflate\u201d its electric vehicle sales figures, instituting a system in which dealers who \u201cplayed ball\u201d were rewarded while those who refused were \u201cpunished,\u201d a new lawsuit alleges. </p>\n<p id=\"XOxdU9\">The lawsuit, which was filed in federal court in Chicago by Napleton Aurora Imports in Illinois and affiliated franchises, says that Hyundai has issued numerous press releases touting the \u201cfake\u201d numbers that purport to show year-over-year growth in EV sales. </p>\n<p id=\"BYnhgV\">Dealers who declined to participate in the alleged ruse were put at a competitive disadvantage, including being forced to push unpopular vehicles or denied wholesale pric", "id": 841122, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195650/hyundai-fake-ev-sales-dealer-lawsuit", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Hyundai dealers pressured to push \u2018fake\u2019 EV sales, lawsuit alleges", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T14:32:22+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bAEPgP8WYBUNoDG8U-iIPrHR77Q=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73453027/Watch_and_Ring_from_Vjeran_Pavic.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image by Alex Parkin / The Verge and Samsung</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"I2GEQ0\">Samsung didn\u2019t just announce <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24194881/samsung-galaxy-unpacked-ring-ai-z-fold-6-flip-watch-7-ultra-buds#stream-entry-669d21f5-39e5-4398-a7fb-3da8f124c566\">new foldable phones</a> and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24194881/samsung-galaxy-unpacked-ring-ai-z-fold-6-flip-watch-7-ultra-buds#stream-entry-cb1241d9-efae-451b-b9e5-16ff3108b8f5\">wireless earbuds</a> during its Samsung Unpacked event on Wednesday but also a new lineup of wearables: the Galaxy Watch 7 ($299.99), the Samsung Ring ($399.99), and the Samsung Galaxy Watch Ultra ($649.99). While you\u2019ll have to wait until July 24th until they\u2019re officially availabl", "id": 841123, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24194952/samsung-galaxy-watch-7-ring-ultra-preorder-buy-price-availability-release-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to preorder Samsung\u2019s Galaxy Watch 7, Galaxy Watch Ultra, and the Galaxy Ring", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Sony ZV-E10 II in white, sitting on a table with its lens detached.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RzXhtCLNqP3vNHyi2owvJdAN2vk=/0x0:7726x5151/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452911/BFARSACE_ZVE10II_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The ZV-E10 II looks a whole lot like its 2021 predecessor.</em></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"7Gv7iG\">Trickle-down economics may be garbage, but Sony remains a steadfast believer when it comes to the tech in its cameras. The new ZV-E10 II continues Sony\u2019s trend of bringing small, iterative changes down from its pricier cameras to more affordable models. Only it\u2019s never without some tradeoffs.</p>\n<p id=\"4LKvq5\">The ZV-E10 II is the APS-C mirrorless system camera follow-up to the original <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22702421/sony-alpha-zv-e10-review-vlogging-camera-test-price-specs\">ZV-E10</a> of 2021, now with a bigger battery, a 26-megapixel backside-illuminated sensor, and improved 4", "id": 841125, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24194506/sony-alpha-zve10ii-vlogging-camera-apsc-mirrorless-specs-price", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sony\u2019s new ZV-E10 II camera is designed to sway vloggers away from $1,000 phones", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of the Supreme Court building with pixelated red and white stripes.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-_j8bu4miMeay7jIXHchVU4QLYw=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452898/STK463_SCOTUS_D.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Here\u2019s what the SCOTUS decision might mean for everything from kids online safety laws to the TikTok \u2018ban.\u2019</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24195235/scotus-netchoice-kosa-kids-safety-age-verification-tiktok-ban\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 841124, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24195235/scotus-netchoice-kosa-kids-safety-age-verification-tiktok-ban", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The aftermath of the Supreme Court\u2019s NetChoice ruling", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"View of Galaxy Watch Ultra\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/lVAlvegcCx6horuGR3JrU5QVcC4=/0x0:4032x2688/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452769/galaxywatchultra4.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>It sure is squircle.</em> | Photo by Victoria Song / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>It\u2019s the Apple Watch Ultra, but for Android. Oh, and the Galaxy Watch 7 is here, too.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24195083/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-7-hands-on-features-price\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 840463, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24195083/samsung-galaxy-watch-ultra-7-hands-on-features-price", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Samsung Galaxy Watch Ultra hands-on: ultra d\u00e9j\u00e0 vu", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Person holding Galaxy Ring in its case\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/YcBPYKFtyCgjtA6ayg_yQa0HEwg=/0x0:8064x5376/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452758/galaxyring5.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>It costs $399.99, there\u2019s no subscription, and it\u2019s generally available starting on July 24th.</em> | Photo by Victoria Song / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The hardware is solid. The ideas are intriguing. So long as it holds up in testing, Samsung could have a winner.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24194938/samsung-galaxy-ring-hands-on-price-unpacked-2024\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 840465, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24194938/samsung-galaxy-ring-hands-on-price-unpacked-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Samsung\u2019s Galaxy Ring could be the one ring to rule an ecosystem", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A hands-on product photo of Samsung\u2019s Galaxy Buds 3 / Galaxy Buds 3 Pro.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/26UyHrvmjER1lhrtKzJzqbOWzsE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452746/DSCF8067_Enhanced_NR.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"UZHf7M\">Alongside its latest folding phones and wearables, Samsung is introducing the new Galaxy Buds 3 Pro and Galaxy Buds 3. As leaks (<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/5/24192554/someone-already-bought-samsungs-galaxy-buds3-pro\">and early sales</a>) confirmed, the company has moved away from the subtle in-ear design of past generations to a stemmed look that gives these an AirPods-esque look and feel \u2014 especially in white. Both earbuds also come in a gunmetal gray finish that, combined with the angular \u201cblade\u201d design, makes me think of Tesla\u2019s Cybertruck. But there\u2019s no denying the overall similarities to Apple\u2019s massively popular AirPods. </p>\n<p id=\"D8k3an\">Samsung\u2019s press release sa", "id": 840464, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24195011/samsung-galaxy-buds-3-pro-hands-on-preview-features", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Samsung\u2019s new Galaxy Buds are blatant AirPod clones in both form and function", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A hands-on photo of Samsung\u2019s Galaxy Z Fold 6 and Flip 6 smartphones.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/I66riB7OyE8CUtS7R-uBM9xNMu4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452748/DSCF8089.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Hot foldable summer is in full swing, y\u2019all.</em> | Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"opCbaW\">If you had any remaining hopes, despite <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/3/24191966/samsung-galaxy-z-fold-flip-6-spec-leak\">leak</a> upon <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/28/24188017/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-fold-6-leak-renders-colors-unpacked\">leak</a>, that Samsung\u2019s foldables would get a major update this year, then I hate to be the bearer of bad news. They\u2019re a little more durable, a little lighter, and come with a handful of tiny upgrades. Even so, both models got a boost of a certain kind: higher prices, with the Galaxy Z Fold 6 now starting at $1,899 and the Z Fl", "id": 840462, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195165/samsung-galaxy-z-fold-flip-6-screen-battery-price", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Galaxy Z Fold 6 and Flip 6 come with minor updates and higher prices", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T12:32:17+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Samsung\u2019s logo on a black, blue, and aqua background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/j30lXEiclgq_A3r3_h4CIMAulZo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452722/acastro_STK075_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>Samsung prepares to talk foldables and AI, and likely a lot more.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24194881/samsung-galaxy-unpacked-ring-ai-z-fold-6-flip-watch-7-ultra-buds\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 839914, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24194881/samsung-galaxy-unpacked-ring-ai-z-fold-6-flip-watch-7-ultra-buds", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Samsung Galaxy Unpacked: all the news on the summer product event", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T12:20:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a crane moving a brain out of a smart home.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RpIoVtoh6HQXRpRzLi93guAMplY=/1x0:3481x2320/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452698/247132_SMART_HOME_MOVE_JGibbs.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Jackson Gibbs for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Moving out of and into a smart home requires a lot of attention to detail.\u00a0This guide will help you through it.\u00a0</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24184716/moving-smart-home-tech-setup\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 839915, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24184716/moving-smart-home-tech-setup", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to move a smart home", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T12:00:13+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of two professional movers carrying belongings in cardboard boxes that are falling apart.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sQMeGeuHX7pBJln9y_rWxvkvzi4=/0x1:4054x2704/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452675/247132_CARDBOARD_BOXES_JGibbs.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Jackson Gibbs for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Renting bins is convenient, slightly more sustainable, and not once did I miss cardboard boxes.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24176469/moving-boxes-plastic-bins-cardboard\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 839916, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24176469/moving-boxes-plastic-bins-cardboard", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Plastic bins: better than boxes", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A still photo from season 2 of Severance.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/i2Ihs_4wgOv-daht1PdGhySWVZI=/716x0:3125x1606/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452644/SEV2_first_look_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"59SmZ0\">The \u201cMusic Dance Experience\u201d is on its way back. Apple just released the first teaser trailer for the much-anticipated second season of <em>Severance</em>, along with the news that the show won\u2019t be returning until 2025. The first episode will start streaming on Apple TV Plus on January 17th and last 10 episodes.</p>\n<p id=\"V0D2b6\">The short teaser doesn\u2019t reveal much about what to expect in the new season, but according to Apple, \u201cMark (Adam Scott) and his friends learn the dire consequences of trifling with the severance barrier, leading them further down a path of woe.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"FsBfSn\">A day before the trailer dropped, Apple released an appropriately cryptic teaser:</", "id": 839917, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23268501/severance-season-2-trailer-date-apple-tv-plus", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Severance season 2 starts streaming in January \u2014 here\u2019s the first teaser", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T11:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A stylized chevron pointed downward, with a silhouette of the Eiffel Tower beneath it.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/T_hZqtadoTsDoFH2Kz-5GY1Y3lE=/57x0:1089x688/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452572/Screenshot_2024_07_08_at_3.15.13_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Samsung</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"KQJ0cd\">Samsung will trot out its next foldables and some new Galaxy AI features during the summer edition of its Galaxy Unpacked event in Paris, France, on Wednesday. You can expect a new Galaxy Z Fold 6 with a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/28/24188017/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-fold-6-leak-renders-colors-unpacked\">squarish look</a> and a not-square Z Flip 6, both with <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/3/24191966/samsung-galaxy-z-fold-flip-6-spec-leak\">much brighter screens and longer battery life</a> than their predecessors.</p>\n<p id=\"grFlSh\">Based on recent leaks, the company will announce new <a href=\"", "id": 839918, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24194483/samsung-galaxy-unpacked-watch-live-stream-start-time", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Where to watch Samsung\u2019s Galaxy Unpacked event on Wednesday", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T10:57:16+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"TOPSHOT-SKOREA-SAMSUNG-STRIKE\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LPAm8fMQW7F168kwZwheXVZBdGE=/100x0:7087x4658/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452568/2160498481.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>NSEU officials said 6,500 Samsung workers participated in the initial three-day walkout \u2014 and now it\u2019s rallying more of its members.</em> | Photo by JUNG YEON-JE/AFP via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"t4aGSJ\">Unionized workers at Samsung Electronics in South Korea have indefinitely extended the first-ever strike at the company in a push for better pay and benefits. The National Samsung Electronics Union (NSEU) rallied its over 30,000 members on Wednesday after the company\u2019s leadership showed no indication of holding talks with the union following <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/8/24194011/thousands-strike-at-samsung\">a three-day walkout</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"yXpkKu\">As reported by <a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/technology", "id": 839919, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/10/24195541/samsung-union-launch-indefinite-strike-ai-chips-pay", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Thousands of Samsung workers launch indefinite strike over pay", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-10T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Image of the Google \u201cG\u201d logo on a blue, black, and purple background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yr7YcXHmCIpyUxkRVQp_CtdLz9I=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73452506/STK093_Google_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bB7CNL\">Google has made it a li